==English==
===Proper noun===
'''Stancel'''

# an [[English]] [[surname]]
# a rare [[male]] [[given name]] derived from the surname

===Etymology===
Stancel is a name that probably comes from:

#Old English ''stane cell'' which means "stone chamber". It could also possibly come from Stancil, a village in England. 
#Polish-Jewish Stencel
#German Stenzel.
#Russian Stanislav/ Polish Stanislaw
#Romanian stanca meaning rock or cliff

===Pronunciation===
*STAN-sull (emphasis on the STAN)
*STAN-sell